Sasalin shot out a jet of flame, setting a small patch of forest on fire, and then circled above, watching for the right moment. Oddly enough, when he slowed down, the strange screeching sound behind him also stopped. Sasalin forgot he had a passenger on his back.
"Come on, Tenuk, you've turned into a Slakor before!"
"There's a big difference between flying yourself and being suddenly dragged by a huge pink dragon!"
"Not bad, Kael?"
Kael clearly disagreed with Nisi's statement. He looked paler than usual, and his claws had dug deeply into Sasalin's back, drawing blood from the Slakor, but Sasalin didn't seem to care. Nevertheless, Sasalin realized he had scared his new friend and landed in an open space.
"Sorry, sorry, I smell a strange odor. I need to deal with it!"
"Why did you have to bring us along too?" Tenuk climbed down from Sasalin's back, sliding to the ground along the tail, and asked sharply. "We left Retevik behind! We abandoned that strong and aggressive big guy! How could he possibly find us?"
"He'll figure it out..." Nisi nodded with a snort. "Retevik may be slow, but he's not stupid."
"Then can Retevik drive a car?"
"Nisi blinked his eyes and turned to look at Tenuk. "Of course he can drive."
"Have you ever seen Retwick drive a car? He doesn't have a truck like yours, and I've never seen him drive a cute little car like Kayer's. He started taking the bus to work purely because you always drove us to work. He only has a bicycle."
A burst of laughter interrupted them. Sasilin suddenly burst into laughter, but no one knew what he was laughing at. Sasilin took a while to calm down.
"Sorry sorry, I just imagined it. Your big, armored friend riding a bike designed specifically for Temson children. That image was so ridiculous! I wish I had telepathy. This idea is so amusing! I must treasure it well."
Kayer also laughed, because he could imagine what Sasilin was thinking. "Well, well. But what did you smell? Why did you fly so fast?"
Sasilin grunted, took off and disappeared quickly, then came back and left a corpse in front of Nixi. It was an Oroslarac, a very rare golden-white dragon-like creature. But its head was missing. "Another one is dead. I heard their cries. I smelled their blood. I must protect them and hunt the killer. This is the will of Ixini. Those creatures are nearby."
The powerful Slak people suddenly froze. Nisi and Kayer also froze, their attention drawn to a gap at the edge of the open space. A huge and pitch-black creature was staring at them, making hissing sounds. The creature suddenly spread its two pairs of massive wings and charged forward, its target clearly Sasalin, completely ignoring the three little figures standing between it and Sasalin. Kayer and Tenuk barely managed to dodge aside, but Nisi found herself dragged to the ground, nearly being flung onto Sasalin.
Sasalin grabbed Nisi and used its long and agile tail to throw her onto its back, then took to the air. The black creature with two pairs of wings quickly chased after them.
Kayer grunted, pulled out his rifle from behind, opened the bag, and took out a belt of bullets. He hung the belt around his chest for easy access, but soon realized that Nisi, Sasalin, and the monster were all gone.
"Hey, Tenuk, can you transform into a flying animal?" Kayer asked.
"Do you want to chase after them?"
“Nonsense.”
“But… one of them is a giant monster!”
“So what? The rifle in my hands is powerful and ready to fire at any moment. I just need to see it, and I can bring it down.”
Tenuk hesitated for a moment, then took a step back, giving himself some space. With a low, slightly painful groan, Tenuk's body stretched out, his fur turning into scales, his arms transforming into wings. He soon became an ordinary light blue Slark, but his eyes remained red.
“Come on up.”
Tenku now looks like an ordinary Slark, with neatly arranged scales growing on his back and a pair of spikes to help Kayel grab him. Tenku took a long time to fly up, but once he was airborne, he quickly adjusted his direction and tried hard to catch up.
However, Tenku and Kayel soon realized they were not the only opponents. A second dark monster burst out from below them, and Tenku barely dodged the impact.
"I guess this is the other terrifying big monster that Larnex was worried about?" Kayel frowned, trying to shoot at the second monster but missed, and quickly reloaded.
Tenku didn't respond; he was busy flying toward Nisi and Sasalin, although another monster was chasing them. Kayel awkwardly turned around to face the monster. The monster was chasing them, and Kayel thought it was good news because it made it easier to aim and shoot. Two bullets pierced the monster's upper wing, and it howled in pain before disappearing into the woods. Kayel wasn't sure if it was still following them, but he thought it was definitely too slow to keep up.
Up ahead, Sasalin was frantically flailing his body and spewing fire at the black monster, while Nisi desperately held onto Sasalin to prevent him from falling. Although this monster was definitely injured, it seemed to be enraged and unwilling to retreat, and the fireballs didn't seem to cause much damage. After Sasalin steadied himself, Nisi took the opportunity to pull out his weapon, a shotgun he trusted. Of course, a shotgun wouldn't be effective against such a monster, but the scattered bullets at least might scare off this black beast?
